Animal Rescue KZN recently reached out to dog owners of the Inanda community, providing guidance and education on proper animal care as well as food and new dog houses provided by Terri Cranke, for their pets. This campaign will be an ongoing in which members of Animal Rescue KZN hold monthly feeding schemes for strays and also spreading awareness on animal welfare to the community and local schools in the area. Pictured is Kandice Naidoo, field operative Animal Rescue KZN, in the Inanda community. 